      • importModel

        void importModel(Validation validation,
                 InputStream inputStream)
        Associates a validation report with the BioPAX data and creates the in-memory model (Paxtools Model). The validation result is object where all the problems related to this data instance are collected.
        Parameters:
        validation -
        inputStream -

      • associate

        void associate(Object element,
               Validation validation)
        Associates an object, such as BioPAX model, element, InputStream; with the given validation result. Some errors may occur during the data import but before the model is created, e.g., those in the XML/RDF header or software bugs. And we want to report these problems as well.
        Parameters:
        element - object (e.g., existing Model)
        validation -

      • indirectlyAssociate

        void indirectlyAssociate(Object parent,
                         Object child)
        Associates, e.g., a property value with validation results by using the 'parent' element to find it. This allows for errors to be reported while model is being read, maybe before the child element is added to the model.
        Parameters:
        parent - BioPAX element
        child - value

      • findValidation

        Collection<Validation> findValidation(Object obj)
        Given the object, finds the corresponding validations (that it's been associated with).
        Parameters:
        obj - a BioPAX element, Model, or even SimpleIOHandler
        Returns:

      • validate

        void validate(Validation validation)
        Post-model validation. The result also includes other problems that might occur during the model initialization and creation.
        Parameters:
        validation -

      • report

        void report(Object obj,
            String errorCode,
            String reportedBy,
            boolean isFixed,
            Object... args)
        Adds the validation error (with proper attributes) to registered validation objects associated with the object.
        Parameters:
        obj - object associated with a validation result (can be even InputStream, during import, but usually is a BioPAX element)
        errorCode - error code
        reportedBy - class name of a validation rule or a name of another BioPAX validating class, method (e.g., AOP aspect's method/joinpoint name).
        isFixed - if true, - find and set the attribute
        args -
